This paper is about using reinforcement learning for robot control, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of sample-based approximate planning methods and parallelization, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions controlling an autonomous vehicle, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) if the robot is using visual input to make decisions.
